), pp. 53-61; Parmesan, C., Climate and species' range (1996) Nature, 382, pp. 765-766; Parmesan, C., Ryrholm, N., Stefanescus, C., Hill, J.K., Thomas, C.D., Descimon, H., Huntley, B., Warren, M., Poleward shifts in geographical ranges of butterfly species associated with regional warming (1999) Nature, 399, pp. 579-583; Sæther, B.-E., Tufto, J., Engen, S., Jerstad, K., Røstad, O.W., Skåtan, J.E., Population dynamical consequences of climate change for a small temperate songbird (2000) Science, 287, pp. 854-856; Sakai, A., Larcher, W., (1987) Frost Survival of Plants, 62. , Ecological Studies, Springer, Berlin; Schmid, E., (1956) Flora des Südens, 2. , Ed. Rascher, Zürich; Spinedi, F., (1991) Il clima del Ticino della mesolcina con accenni di climatologia generale (The Climate of the Mesolcina of Ticino and Some General Climatic Aspects), , Arbeitsberichte der Schweizerischen Meteorologischen Anstalt, Zürich; Thompson, K., Hodgson, J.G., Rich, T.C.G., Native and alien invasive plants: More of the same? (1995) Ecography, 18, pp. 390-402; Walker, B.H., Steffen, W.L., Canadell, J., Ingram, J.S.I., (1999) The Terrestrial Biosphere and Global Change, , (eds.) IGBP Book Series 4. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Walther, G.-R., Distribution and limits of evergreen broad-leaved (laurophyllous) species in Switzerland (1999) Bot Helv, 109, pp. 153-167; Walther, G.-R., Climatic forcing on the dispersal of exotic species (2000) Phytocoenologia, 30, pp. 409-430; Walther, G.-R., Laurophyllisation - A sign for a changing climate? (2001) Biomonitoring: General and Applied Aspects on Regional and Global Scales, pp. 207-223. , Burga C.A. and Kratochwil A. (eds.) Tasks for vegetation science 35, Kluwer, Dordrecht; Walther, G.-R., Burga, C.A., Edwards, P.J., (2001) ""Fingerprints"" of Climate Change - Adapted Behaviour and Shifting Species Ranges, , (eds.) Kluwer, New York, London; Woodward, F.I., (1987) Climate and Plant Distribution, , Cambridge University Press, London; Zelle